# API Design & Backward Compatibility - Freshworks Integration

Design typed APIs for external services (Freshsales, ElevenLabs, Telnyx) and internal services with explicit contracts, validation, and backward compatibility guarantees.

**Justification:** Reliable API integrations prevent service outages and simplify debugging in production CRM environments.

## External API Clients

### Client Library Structure
- Export typed interfaces for all request/response objects
- Include builder functions for complex request payloads (`buildOutboundCallBody`)
- Document required vs optional fields clearly
- Handle authentication consistently across clients

### Error Handling
- Standardize error responses across different providers
- Include retry logic for transient failures
- Log API failures with context for debugging

### Examples from This Project
```typescript
// Good: Explicit types and builder pattern
export interface OutboundCallRequest {
  agentId: string;
  phoneNumberId: string;
  toNumber: string;
}

export function buildOutboundCallBody(req: OutboundCallRequest): Record<string, unknown> {
  return {
    agent_id: req.agentId,
    agent_phone_number_id: req.phoneNumberId,
    to_number: req.toNumber,
  };
}
```

## Internal Service APIs

### Endpoint Design
- Use explicit TypeScript types for request/response bodies
- Validate inputs using schema validation (Zod, Joi, or similar)
- Return consistent error response formats
- Include health check endpoints (`/healthz`)

### Authentication & Security
- Use Bearer token authentication for webhook endpoints
- Validate secrets and API keys securely
- Log security events appropriately

### Real-time APIs (WebSocket/WebRTC)
- Define clear message schemas with discriminated unions
- Handle connection lifecycle events properly
- Include conversation/session management

### Backward Compatibility
- Avoid breaking changes to existing endpoints
- Use optional fields for new features
- Version APIs when breaking changes are necessary
- Document deprecation timelines

### Examples from This Project
```typescript
// Good: Explicit request/response types
type PersonalizeBody = {
  system__caller_id?: string;
  caller?: string;
  freshsales_contact_id?: number | string | null;
  [k: string]: unknown;
};

// Good: Consistent error handling
if (secret && auth !== `Bearer ${secret}`) {
  return reply.code(401).send({ error: 'unauthorized' });
}
```

## Type Safety & Validation

- Use discriminated unions for polymorphic responses
- Validate external data at boundaries
- Export all public types from package index files
- Consider runtime type validation for critical paths

